name: PlanB
tweet: @stockomatics time models are similar to s2f in that they are also linear regression models, but different in that they have time and not s2f ration as an input variable.  S2F model: BTC = a*S2Fratio^b Time model: BTC=a*time^b  time can be measured as number of days/months since Jan 2009.

name: PlanB
tweet: I get messages from people asking if the current 51% attack on BSV coin could also happen to #bitcoin ...  That is NOT the case! BTC hashrate (~100EH/s) is 1000X higher than BSV (~0.1EH/s). See chart: orange line bottom right near X-axis is BSV (forked in 2018), blue line is BTC.  https://t.co/myvAEM9vn3

name: PlanB
tweet: @Criptomaniaco8 @tsypruyan s2f = current BTC stock (18.8M) divided by annual BTC production (~12*24*6*6.25). s2f is not impacted by whether miners hold or sell.

name: PlanB
tweet: @CryptoVizArt @glassnode Interesting!  There are indeed more variables that impact btc price than only s2f. Indeed an extra variable reflecting greed&fear (bull&bear) will correlate with s2f model error, and explain autocorrelation and heteroscedasticity. I found lost coin correction to have less impact.

name: PlanB
tweet: #bitcoin realized cap is rising again! Realized cap is the average price at which all 18.77M BTC were last transacted (calculated over all utxo's). Also, the few sellers at the moment sell at a profit (not a loss like in May and June). IMO this is bullish.  https://t.co/q3mhSZ19oH

tweet: @just_buy_link It's about capital treatment for banks investing in bitcoin. So they have to hold $1 capital for every $1 btc. This means they cannot use saving money or other loans to buy bitcoin, i.e. no leverage.

tweet: 13. As I see $ETH as the new world infrastructure, I see #BTC as digital gold.   With such an increase in institutional demand over the last year, apparently only 59 companies hold #Bitcoin on their balance sheet.   https://t.co/WHtB2HABEk

name: MacroCRG
tweet: 6. Weeks of relentless FUD from all angles after #BTC broke down from a 'distribution' range.... I believe it was it was coordinated.   Another reason why I believe we haven't seen the top of this macro bullish cycle is #DeFi.

name: MacroCRG
tweet: 3. The fact we didn't see a 'blow off top' on this recent #BTC top adds credence to this belief.   A blow off top & 'mania phase' usually signals a long term top - when price seriously detaches from fundamentals. We arguably saw a meme coin mania phase, but not for #DeFi or #BTC.

name: MacroCRG
tweet: 2. This would lead to faster market cycles, which I believe we're seeing right now. A market cycle within a market cycle.   IMO institutional investors or large investors from #TradFi taking profit & looking to re-enter w/ better R:R played a large role in this recent #BTC top.

name: MacroCRG
tweet: 1. This bullish cycle has brought huge institutional demand.  In #TradFi, an annual rate of return of 10% is typically deemed as good ROI... so if 100%+ returns are seen in #BTC or $crypto (as was/is the case), profit taking is highly likely...

tweet: Basically, Sovryn is a "Bitcoinized" version of DeFi.  No sign-up, hold your own keys, and trade on a BTC-secured chain that allows fees to be paid in BTC.  They're the blue-chip of BTC DeFi, and where could it go if they get just 10% of ETH DeFi's market share?

name: The Crypto Dogüìà
tweet: Sovryn is the first real & usable example of BTC DeFi.  They're a DEX that offers permissionless leveraged trading/lending built around a BTC-secured chain.  (‚ùóÔ∏èThis is not a knock on ETH; I love ETH DeFi and believe competition only makes the space greater overall.)

name: The Crypto Dogüìà
tweet: BTC DeFi is interesting bc it can do valuable DeFi things but on a BTC-secured chain, which gives hardline Bitcoiners a gateway to DeFi.  The $SOV team is wicked smart, dedicated, and appeals to the Bitcoin community (a powerful and not insignificant force to be reckoned with).

name: //Bitcoin ùïµack üêê
tweet: @Zettt As premiums rise, it becomes more attractive to lend out btc, but for the time being the available btc to borrow keeps going down - it becomes the dominant factor in high rates

name: //Bitcoin ùïµack üêê
tweet: @Zettt It's a lending market - if more people were willing to lend out BTC, the premium would be lower. People want to borrow BTC, few want to lend it. If the underlying is seeing heavy reduction in traded supply (accumulation), there is less available to borrow, funding goes up.

tweet: Thanks @CourtReagan & @GuyAdami for inviting me on @CNBCFastMoney to discuss our #Bitcoin strategy, increasing institutional adoption of BTC vs. Gold as an inflation hedge, $MSTR capital markets strategy, and the future of the crypto-industry.

name: Michael Saylor‚ö°Ô∏è
tweet: The 21st century global monetary solution is a digital currency (USD) serving as a medium of exchange backed by a digital asset (BTC) serving as a store of value, with #Bitcoin as the final settlement network and #Lightning as the transaction network.  El Salvador is the model.
